│ The user wants me to fix a crash in the LLVM `gvn` pass.                                                                     │
│ The crash is triggered by an `llvm.assume` that an `alloca` pointer is `null`. This is a contradiction, as `alloca` can      │
│ never be null.                                                                                                               │
│ The `gvn` pass propagates this assumption, replacing the `alloca` with `null` in subsequent `llvm.lifetime.start` and        │
│ `llvm.lifetime.end` calls.                                                                                                   │
│ This creates invalid IR, as `llvm.lifetime.*` intrinsics require an `alloca` or `poison` value as their pointer argument,    │
