│                                                                                                                              │
│ The core issue is that GVN is too aggressive in propagating the `null` value from a contradictory assumption. While          │
│ `assume(false)` can be used to mark code as unreachable, replacing a non-nullable pointer like an `alloca` with `null` can   │
│ break invariants of other IR constructs.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ A good fix would be to make GVN aware of the non-nullable nature of `alloca` instructions. When GVN processes an             │
│ `assume(icmp eq %alloca, null)`, it should recognize this as a contradiction. Instead of propagating `null` as the value for │
│ `%alloca`, it should treat the code path following the assume as unreachable. This can be achieved by replacing the `assume` │
│ with a call to `unreachable`.                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will modify the `GVN::processAssume` function in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVN.cpp`.                                     │
│ Specifically, when `processAssume` encounters a comparison `(LHS == RHS)` or `(LHS != RHS)`, and one of the operands is an   │
│ `AllocaInst` and the other is a `ConstantPointerNull`, I will check for the contradictory case.                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ If the assumption is `alloca == null`, it's a contradiction. I will replace the `assume` call with an `unreachable`          │
│ instruction and mark the block's successors as dead. This correctly models the semantics of `assume(false)`.                 │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ If the assumption is `alloca != null`, this is always true. The `assume` is redundant and can be safely removed.             │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ This change will prevent GVN from creating invalid IR for `llvm.lifetime.*` intrinsics and handle the contradictory          │
│ assumption correctly.                                                                                                        │
