│ The problem originates in `GVNPass::propagateEquality` (line 2538). This function is called to process the condition of an   │
│ `llvm.assume`. In the bug's case, it's called with `LHS = (%icmp eq %alloca, null)` and `RHS = true`. The function correctly │
│ deduces that this implies `%alloca == null`. It then adds `(%alloca, null)` to its worklist and proceeds to replace uses of  │
│ the alloca with null, which is incorrect and leads to a crash.                                                               │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The fix is to detect this specific contradictory case inside `propagateEquality`. When we deduce an equivalence (`A == B`),  │
│ and one operand is an `AllocaInst` and the other is a `ConstantPointerNull`, we know this is a contradiction. An `alloca`    │
│ can never be null. Instead of propagating this false equality, we should do nothing. This prevents the incorrect             │
│ transformation.                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will insert a check at the point where the equivalence is detected and added to the worklist. This is inside the `if       │
│ (CmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(LHS))` block, right before `Worklist.push_back`.                                           │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The correct line for insertion is after `Value *Op0 = Cmp->getOperand(0), *Op1 = Cmp->getOperand(1);` and before `if         │
│ (Cmp->isEquivalence(IsKnownFalse))`. This is around line 2656.                                                               │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i '2656i\                                                                                                               │
│       if ((isa<AllocaInst>(Op0) && isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Op1)) ||\                                                        │
